A Fine Romance is a British situation comedy starring husband-and-wife team Judi Dench and Michael Williams .
Dench 's sister and brother-in-law were played by Susan Penhaligon and Richard Warwick .
It was produced by London Weekend Television and written by Bob Larbey .
It was first broadcast on 8 November 1981 .
It lasted for 26 episodes over four series ; the final episode being broadcast on 17 February 1984 .
The series takes its name from a song in the 1936 film Swing Time , starring Fred Astaire and Ginger Rogers , which Dench recorded as the theme music .
The series was nominated for nine BAFTA British Academy Television Awards and a winner of two , both for Dench 's performance in 1982 and 1985 .